entry.sense:
[5. tZb-I, if used, means He acted like the ZaboI, or gazelle; being similar to tacaO-aba and tanam-ara, &c.: 
its part. n. is mentioned in the first paragraph {1} 
of art. rbD.]

hom.sense:
And AZrf fiI AlEibaArapi is explainable 
[as meaning He was elegant, or eloquent, in the expression, or phrase, or speech], 
if the saying be received from those who are trustworthy: if not, it is correctly OaTorafa, with the unpointed T; meaning “he said what was novel and pleasing.” (Mgh.)

entry.sense:
4. AZEnhu 
He made him to journey, go away, depart, (Ṣ, Mṣb, Ḳ,) or remove; 
and ZaEana↓ bihi signifies the same [or he journeyed,, &c., with him]. (Mṣb.)

hom.sense:
maZofuwrN; 
and its fem.: 
see ZafirN.

maZofuwrN bihi Overcome, or conquered; 
[as also maZofuwrN Ealayohi, and maZofuwrN alone; 
(see 1;)] 
applied to a man. (TA.)

4. AZl-, said of a day, It was, (Ṣ, O,) or became, (M, Ḳ,) shady, or a day having shade: (Ṣ, M, O, Ḳ:) or it was a day having clouds, or other [causes of shade]: (T:) or it was continually shady; 
as also Zal-a↓, aor. yaZil-u, 
inf. n. ZilaAlapN. (Mṣb.)

entry.sense:
muZil-N A thing having shade; by means of which one shades himself; 
as also muZal-ilN↓. (Mṣb.) 
And [A cloudy day;] a day having clouds: or having continual shade. (TA.)

hom.sense:
And [Declining from the truth, or from that which is right; 
(see ZalaEN;)] 
committing a sin, crime, fault, or misdeed. (TA.)

entry.sense:
Zan-aAnN One who opines, or conjectures, much 
[and] in an evil manner; 
as also ZunanN↓. (TA.)

hom.sense:
AZhr signifies also He entered upon the time called the Zahiyrap: (A, Mṣb, Ḳ:) or the time called the Zuhor. (Mṣb.) 
And He went, or journeyed, in the time called the Zahiyrap; 
as also Zh-r↓, (Ḳ,) inf. n. taZohiyrN: (TA:) or the time called the Zuhor. (Ṣ, O.)
